any products u could find in your home that makes hair shine thanks try to use a vinegar mix six tablespoons of vinegar into your shampoo and leave on for minutes rinse thoroughly the vinegar will not only enhance highlights but also gives hair a super shiny finish blonds white vinegar darker blondes balsamic vinegar brunettes red wine vinegar redheads raspberry flavored vinegar tea and beer improve the look of the hair and are easy to do begin by boiling two servings of tea leaves either loose or by opening two tea bags and placing the contents in the pot strain the leaves from the liquid and allow it to cool apply to hair as a rinse after shampooing and gently comb the tea through the hair for a minute or two rinse lightly and then style your hair as normal beer also gives the hair body and makes it more manageable pour a bottle of beer over the hair working it with your fingers for a few minutes rinse well and style you will notice that both the tea and the beer will give your hair a lot more shine bounce and body also you could try cup of honey with two tablespoons of olive oil mix well and massage into hair cover it with a shower cap for mins shampoo and rinse well hair will be silky smooth and shiny Vinegar Shampoo Beer Wine Brewery Mayonnaise Haggis Tofu Sento Coffee Cuisine of the Philippines Teapot Pottery Chinese tea culture Japanese tea ceremony Sake Barbecue Bread Jewish cuisine Yerba mate Rum Alcoholic beverage Honey German cuisine Korean cuisine Cheese Herbal tea Soap Menstrual cup Cuisine of Denmark Sushi Food preservation Hong Kong-style milk tea Hair Japanese cuisine Black tea Massage Balsamic vinegar Olive oil Acetic acid Plastic Birch Wine making Dandruff Ale Caffeine Soap bubble Leaf Hair conditioner Moonshine Dim sum Fast bowling Chili con carne Bong Cider Hair color Gumbo Breastfeeding 613 mitzvot Hard water Casting Champagne (beverage) Characters of Naruto Gelatin Red hair Top-bar hive Wheat beer First aid Halitosis Fujian tea ceremony Scotch 